				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Well, if you're willing to go with horizontal, you have a lot more freedom... You don't need sprites, and you don't need the image to move between frames, or even empty lines between rows, and you don't even have to interleave frames of the animation. You can just double or triple or quadruple arbitrary scanlines. Obviously it's not the same effect at all, at that point, but if your goal is lower-resolution frames of animation, that's one way to do it.<br /><br />Of course you can also make blank scanlines, with the spatial displacement, etc. with pretty much the same technique, just at this point there's no technical reason why they have to be blank.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
